gitoid.name: gitoid
gitoid.summary: https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid Gitoid stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects) and a gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent the software [Artifact ID](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-id) or the [OmniBOR Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#omnibor-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [OmniBOR Document](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#omnibor-document); this ambiguity exists because the OmniBOR Document is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Omnibor is a minimalistic schema to describe software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg). Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's ContentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the OmniBOR Document (OmniBOR Identifiers) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's ExternalIdentifier property.

swhid.name: swhid
swhid.summary: SoftWare Hash IDentifier, persistent intrinsic identifiers for digital artifacts, such as files, trees (also known as directories or folders), commits, and other objects typically found in version control systems. The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [SWHID specification](https://www.swhid.org/specification/v1.1/4.Syntax) and they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

hasConcludedLicense.name: hasConcludedLicense
hasConcludedLicense.summary: The `from` Software Artifact is concluded by the SPDX data creator to be governed by each `to` license

hasDataFile.name: hasDataFile
hasDataFile.summary: The `from` Element treats each `to` Element as a data file

hasDeclaredLicense.name: hasDeclaredLicense
hasDeclaredLicense.summary: The `from` Software Artifact was discovered to actually contain each `to` license, for example as detected by use of automated tooling.

hasDeletedFile.name: hasDeletedFile
hasDeletedFile.summary: Every `to` Element is a file deleted from the `from` Element (`from` hasDeletedFile `to`)

hasDependencyManifest.name: hasDependencyManifest
hasDependencyManifest.summary: The `from` Element has manifest files that contain dependency information in each `to` Element

hasDistributionArtifact.name: hasDistributionArtifact
hasDistributionArtifact.summary: The `from` Element is distributed as an artifact in each Element `to`, (e.g. an RPM or archive file)

hasDocumentation.name: hasDocumentation
hasDocumentation.summary: The `from` Element is documented by each `to` Element

hasDynamicLink.name: hasDynamicLink
hasDynamicLink.summary: The `from` Element dynamically links in each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

hasEvidence.name: hasEvidence
hasEvidence.summary: (Dataset) Every `to` Element is considered as evidence for the `from` Element (`from` hasEvidence `to`)

hasExample.name: hasExample
hasExample.summary: Every `to` Element is an example for the `from` Element (`from` hasExample `to`)

hasHost.name: hasHost
hasHost.summary: The `from` Build was run on the `to` Element during a LifecycleScopeType period (e.g. The host that the build runs on)

hasInputs.name: hasInputs
hasInputs.summary: The `from` Build has each `to` Elements as an input during a LifecycleScopeType period.

hasMetadata.name: hasMetadata
hasMetadata.summary: Every `to` Element is metadata about the `from` Element (`from` hasMetadata `to`)

hasOptionalComponent.name: hasOptionalComponent
hasOptionalComponent.summary: Every `to` Element is an optional component of the `from` Element (`from` hasOptionalComponent` `to`)

hasOptionalDependency.name: hasOptionalDependency
hasOptionalDependency.summary: The `from` Element optionally depends on each `to` Element during a LifecycleScopeType period

hasOutputs.name: hasOutputs
hasOutputs.summary: The `from` Build element generates each `to` Element as an output during a LifecycleScopeType period.

hasPrerequsite.name: hasPrerequsite
hasPrerequsite.summary: The `from` Element has a prerequsite on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period

hasProvidedDependency.name: hasProvidedDependency
hasProvidedDependency.summary: The `from` Element has a dependency on each `to` Element, but dependency is not in the distributed artifact, but assumed to be provided, during a LifecycleScopeType period

hasRequirement.name: hasRequirement
hasRequirement.summary: The `from` Element has a requirement on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period

hasSpecification.name: hasSpecification
hasSpecification.summary: Every `to` Element is a specification for the `from` Element (`from` hasSpecification `to`), during a LifecycleScopeType period

hasStaticLink.name: hasStaticLink
hasStaticLink.summary: The `from` Element statically links in each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period

hasTest.name: hasTest
hasTest.summary: Every `to` Element is a test artifact for the `from` Element (`from` hasTest `to`), during a LifecycleScopeType period

hasTestCase.name: hasTestCase
hasTestCase.summary: Every `to` Element is a test case for the `from` Element (`from` hasTestCase `to`)

hasVariant.name: hasVariant
hasVariant.summary: Every `to` Element is a variant the `from` Element (`from` hasVariant `to`)

invokedBy.name: invokedBy
invokedBy.summary: The `from` Element was invoked by the `to` Agent during a LifecycleScopeType period (for example, a Build element that describes a build step)

modifiedBy.name: modifiedBy
modifiedBy.summary: The `from` Element is modified by each `to` Element

other.name: other
other.summary: Every `to` Element is related to the `from` Element where the relationship type is not described by any of the SPDX relationhip types (this relationship is directionless)

packagedBy.name: packagedBy
packagedBy.summary: Every `to` Element is a packaged instance of the `from` Element (`from` packagedBy `to`)

patchedBy.name: patchedBy
patchedBy.summary: Every `to` Element is a patch for the `from` Element (`from` patchedBy `to`)

publishedBy.name: publishedBy
publishedBy.summary: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability was made available for public use or reference by each `to` Agent

reportedBy.name: reportedBy
reportedBy.summary: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability was first reported to a project, vendor, or tracking database for formal identification by each `to` Agent

republishedBy.name: republishedBy
republishedBy.summary: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability's details were tracked, aggregated, and/or enriched to improve context (i.e. NVD) by a `to` Agent(s)

serializedInArtifact.name: serializedInArtifact
serializedInArtifact.summary: The `from` SPDXDocument can be found in a serialized form in each `to` Artifact

testedOn.name: testedOn
testedOn.summary: (AI, Dataset) The `from` Element has been tested on the `to` Element

trainedOn.name: trainedOn
trainedOn.summary: (AI, Dataset) The `from` Element has been trained by the `to` Element(s)

underInvestigationFor.name: underInvestigationFor
underInvestigationFor.summary: (Security/VEX) The `from` Vulnerability impact is being investigated for each `to` Element

usesTool.name: usesTool
usesTool.summary: The `from` Element uses each `to` Element as a tool during a LifecycleScopeType period.

RelationshipType.name: RelationshipType
RelationshipType.summary: Information about the relationship between two Elements.

deployed.name: deployed
deployed.summary: in addition to being supported by the supplier, the software is known to have been deployed and is in use.  For a software as a service provider, this implies the software is now available as a service.

development.name: development
development.summary: the artifact is in active development and is not considered ready for formal support from the supplier.

endOfSupport.name: endOfSupport
endOfSupport.summary: there is a defined end of support for the artifact from the supplier.  This may also be referred to as end of life. There is a validUntilDate that can be used to signal when support ends for the artifact.

limitedSupport.name: limitedSupport
limitedSupport.summary: the artifact has been released, and there is limited support available from the supplier. There is a validUntilDate that can provide additional information about the duration of support.

noAssertion.name: noAssertion
noAssertion.summary: no assertion about the type of support is made.   This is considered the default if no other support type is used.

noSupport.name: noSupport
noSupport.summary: there is no support for the artifact from the supplier, consumer assumes any support obligations.

support.name: support
support.summary: the artifact has been released, and is supported from the supplier.   There is a validUntilDate that can provide additional information about the duration of support.

SupportType.name: SupportType
SupportType.summary: Indicates the type of support that is associated with an artifact.

DatasetPackage.name: DatasetPackage
DatasetPackage.summary: Specifies a data package and its associated information.

confidentialityLevel.name: confidentialityLevel
confidentialityLevel.summary: Describes the confidentiality level of the data points contained in the dataset.

dataCollectionProcess.name: dataCollectionProcess
dataCollectionProcess.summary: Describes how the dataset was collected.

dataPreprocessing.name: dataPreprocessing
dataPreprocessing.summary: Describes the preprocessing steps that were applied to the raw data to create the given dataset.

datasetAvailability.name: datasetAvailability
datasetAvailability.summary: The field describes the availability of a dataset.

datasetNoise.name: datasetNoise
datasetNoise.summary: Describes potentially noisy elements of the dataset.

datasetSize.name: datasetSize
datasetSize.summary: Captures the size of the dataset.

datasetType.name: datasetType
datasetType.summary: Describes the type of the given dataset.

datasetUpdateMechanism.name: datasetUpdateMechanism
datasetUpdateMechanism.summary: Describes a mechanism to update the dataset.

hasSensitivePersonalInformation.name: hasSensitivePersonalInformation
hasSensitivePersonalInformation.summary: Describes if any sensitive personal information is present in the dataset.

intendedUse.name: intendedUse
intendedUse.summary: Describes what the given dataset should be used for.

knownBias.name: knownBias
knownBias.summary: Records the biases that the dataset is known to encompass.

sensor.name: sensor
sensor.summary: Describes a sensor used for collecting the data.

amber.name: amber
amber.summary: Data points in the dataset can be shared only with specific organizations and their clients on a need to know basis.

clear.name: clear
clear.summary: Dataset may be distributed freely, without restriction.

green.name: green
green.summary: Dataset can be shared within a community of peers and partners.

red.name: red
red.summary: Data points in the dataset are highly confidential and can only be shared with named recipients.

clickthrough.name: clickthrough
clickthrough.summary: the dataset is not publicly available and can only be accessed after affirmatively accepting terms on a clickthrough webpage.

directDownload.name: directDownload
directDownload.summary: the dataset is publicly available and can be downloaded directly.

query.name: query
query.summary: the dataset is publicly available, but not all at once, and can only be accessed through queries which return parts of the dataset.

registration.name: registration
registration.summary: the dataset is not publicly available and an email registration is required before accessing the dataset, although without an affirmative acceptance of terms.

scrapingScript.name: scrapingScript
scrapingScript.summary: the dataset provider is not making available the underlying data and the dataset must be reassembled, typically using the provided script for scraping the data.

audio.name: audio
audio.summary: data is audio based, such as a collection of music from the 80s.

categorical.name: categorical
categorical.summary: data that is classified into a discrete number of categories, such as the eye color of a population of people.

graph.name: graph
graph.summary: data is in the form of a graph where entries are somehow related to each other through edges, such a social network of friends.

image.name: image
image.summary: data is a collection of images such as pictures of animals.

numeric.name: numeric
numeric.summary: data consists only of numeric entries.

other.name: other
other.summary: data is of a type not included in this list.

sensor.name: sensor
sensor.summary: data is recorded from a physical sensor, such as a thermometer reading or biometric device.

structured.name: structured
structured.summary: data is stored in tabular format or retrieved from a relational database.

syntactic.name: syntactic
syntactic.summary: data describes the syntax or semantics of a language or text, such as a parse tree used for natural language processing.

text.name: text
text.summary: data consists of unstructured text, such as a book, Wikipedia article (without images), or transcript.

timeseries.name: timeseries
timeseries.summary: data is recorded in an ordered sequence of timestamped entries, such as the price of a stock over the course of a day.

timestamp.name: timestamp
timestamp.summary: data is recorded with a timestamp for each entry, but not necessarily ordered or at specific intervals, such as when a taxi ride starts and ends.

video.name: video
video.summary: data is video based, such as a collection of movie clips featuring Tom Hanks.

ConjunctiveLicenseSet.name: ConjunctiveLicenseSet
ConjunctiveLicenseSet.summary:
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information
where all elements apply.

CustomLicense.name: CustomLicense
CustomLicense.summary: A license that is not listed on the SPDX License List.

CustomLicenseAddition.name: CustomLicenseAddition
CustomLicenseAddition.summary: A license addition that is not listed on the SPDX Exceptions List.

DisjunctiveLicenseSet.name: DisjunctiveLicenseSet
DisjunctiveLicenseSet.summary:
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information
where only one of the elements applies.

ExtendableLicense.name: ExtendableLicense
ExtendableLicense.summary: Abstract class representing a License or an OrLaterOperator.

IndividualLicensingInfo.name: IndividualLicensingInfo
IndividualLicensingInfo.summary: A concrete subclass of AnyLicenseInfo used by Individuals in the ExpandedLicensing profile.

License.name: License
License.summary: Abstract class for the portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a license.

LicenseAddition.name: LicenseAddition
LicenseAddition.summary:
Abstract class for additional text intended to be added to a License, but
which is not itself a standalone License.

ListedLicense.name: ListedLicense
ListedLicense.summary: A license that is listed on the SPDX License List.

ListedLicenseException.name: ListedLicenseException
ListedLicenseException.summary: A license exception that is listed on the SPDX Exceptions list.

OrLaterOperator.name: OrLaterOperator
OrLaterOperator.summary:
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing this version, or any later version,
of the indicated License.

WithAdditionOperator.name: WithAdditionOperator
WithAdditionOperator.summary:
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a License which has additional
text applied to it.

NoAssertionLicense.name: NoAssertionLicense
NoAssertionLicense.summary: An Individual Value for License when no assertion can be made about its actual value.

NoneLicense.name: NoneLicense
NoneLicense.summary: An Individual Value for License where the SPDX data creator determines that no license is present.

additionText.name: additionText
additionText.summary: Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition.

deprecatedVersion.name: deprecatedVersion
deprecatedVersion.summary:
Specifies the SPDX License List version in which this license or exception
identifier was deprecated.

isDeprecatedAdditionId.name: isDeprecatedAdditionId
isDeprecatedAdditionId.summary: Specifies whether an additional text identifier has been marked as deprecated.

isDeprecatedLicenseId.name: isDeprecatedLicenseId
isDeprecatedLicenseId.summary:
Specifies whether a license or additional text identifier has been marked as
deprecated.

isFsfLibre.name: isFsfLibre
isFsfLibre.summary:
Specifies whether the License is listed as free by the
[Free Software Foundation (FSF)](https://fsf.org).

isOsiApproved.name: isOsiApproved
isOsiApproved.summary:
Specifies whether the License is listed as approved by the
[Open Source Initiative (OSI)](https://opensource.org).

licenseXml.name: licenseXml
licenseXml.summary: Identifies all the text and metadata associated with a license in the license XML format.

listVersionAdded.name: listVersionAdded
listVersionAdded.summary:
Specifies the SPDX License List version in which this ListedLicense or
ListedLicenseException identifier was first added.

member.name: member
member.summary: A license expression participating in a license set.

obsoletedBy.name: obsoletedBy
obsoletedBy.summary:
Specifies the licenseId that is preferred to be used in place of a deprecated
License or LicenseAddition.

seeAlso.name: seeAlso
seeAlso.summary: Contains a URL where the License or LicenseAddition can be found in use.

standardAdditionTemplate.name: standardAdditionTemplate
standardAdditionTemplate.summary: Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition, in SPDX templating format.

standardLicenseHeader.name: standardLicenseHeader
standardLicenseHeader.summary:
Provides a License author's preferred text to indicate that a file is covered
by the License.

standardLicenseTemplate.name: standardLicenseTemplate
standardLicenseTemplate.summary: Identifies the full text of a License, in SPDX templating format.

subjectAddition.name: subjectAddition
subjectAddition.summary: A LicenseAddition participating in a 'with addition' model.

subjectExtendableLicense.name: subjectExtendableLicense
subjectExtendableLicense.summary: A License participating in a 'with addition' model.

subjectLicense.name: subjectLicense
subjectLicense.summary: A License participating in an 'or later' model.

CdxPropertiesExtension.name: CdxPropertiesExtension
CdxPropertiesExtension.summary: A type of extension consisting of a list of name value pairs.

CdxPropertyEntry.name: CdxPropertyEntry
CdxPropertyEntry.summary: A property name with an associated value.

Extension.name: Extension
Extension.summary: A characterization of some aspect of an Element that is associated with the Element in a generalized fashion.

cdxPropName.name: cdxPropName
cdxPropName.summary: A name used in a CdxExtension name-value pair.

cdxPropValue.name: cdxPropValue
cdxPropValue.summary: A value used in a CdxExtension name-value pair.

cdxProperty.name: cdxProperty
cdxProperty.summary: Provides a map of a property names to a values.

CvssV2VulnAssessmentRelationship.name: CvssV2VulnAssessmentRelationship
CvssV2VulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Provides a CVSS version 2.0 assessment for a vulnerability.

CvssV3VulnAssessmentRelationship.name: CvssV3VulnAssessmentRelationship
CvssV3VulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Provides a CVSS version 3 assessment for a vulnerability.

CvssV4VulnAssessmentRelationship.name: CvssV4VulnAssessmentRelationship
CvssV4VulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Provides a CVSS version 4 assessment for a vulnerability.

EpssVulnAssessmentRelationship.name: EpssVulnAssessmentRelationship
EpssVulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Provides an EPSS assessment for a vulnerability.

ExploitCatalogVulnAssessmentRelationship.name: ExploitCatalogVulnAssessmentRelationship
ExploitCatalogVulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Provides an exploit assessment of a vulnerability.

SsvcVulnAssessmentRelationship.name: SsvcVulnAssessmentRelationship
SsvcVulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Provides an SSVC assessment for a vulnerability.

VexAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship.name: VexAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship
VexAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship.summary:
Connects a vulnerability and an element designating the element as a product
affected by the vulnerability.

VexFixedVulnAssessmentRelationship.name: VexFixedVulnAssessmentRelationship
VexFixedVulnAssessmentRelationship.summary:
Links a vulnerability and elements representing products (in the VEX sense) where
a fix has been applied and are no longer affected.

VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship.name: VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship
VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship.summary:
Links a vulnerability and one or more elements designating the latter as products
not affected by the vulnerability.

VexUnderInvestigationVulnAssessmentRelat.name: VexUnderInvestigationVulnAssessmentRelationship
VexUnderInvestigationVulnAssessmentRelat.summary:
Designates elements as products where the impact of a vulnerability is being
investigated.

VexVulnAssessmentRelationship.name: VexVulnAssessmentRelationship
VexVulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Asbtract ancestor class for all VEX relationships

VulnAssessmentRelationship.name: VulnAssessmentRelationship
VulnAssessmentRelationship.summary: Abstract ancestor class for all vulnerability assessments

Vulnerability.name: Vulnerability
Vulnerability.summary: Specifies a vulnerability and its associated information.

actionStatement.name: actionStatement
actionStatement.summary:
Provides advise on how to mitigate or remediate a vulnerability when a VEX product
is affected by it.

actionStatementTime.name: actionStatementTime
actionStatementTime.summary:
Records the time when a recommended action was communicated in a VEX statement 
to mitigate a vulnerability.

assessedElement.name: assessedElement
assessedElement.summary:
Specifies an element contained in a piece of software where a vulnerability was
found.

decisionType.name: decisionType
decisionType.summary: Provide the enumeration of possible decisions in the Stakeholder-Specific Vulnerability Categorization (SSVC) decision tree [https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/cisa-ssvc-guide%20508c.pdf](https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/cisa-ssvc-guide%20508c.pdf)

exploited.name: exploited
exploited.summary: Describe that a CVE is known to have an exploit because it's been listed in an exploit catalog.

impactStatement.name: impactStatement
impactStatement.summary:
Explains why a VEX product is not affected by a vulnerability. It is an
alternative in VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship to the machine-readable
justification label.

justificationType.name: justificationType
justificationType.summary:
Impact justification label to be used when linking a vulnerability to an element
representing a VEX product with a VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship
relationship.

locator.name: locator
locator.summary: Provides the location of an exploit catalog.

modifiedTime.name: modifiedTime
modifiedTime.summary: Specifies a time when a vulnerability assessment was modified

percentile.name: percentile
percentile.summary: The percentile of the current probability score.

probability.name: probability
probability.summary: A probability score between 0 and 1 of a vulnerability being exploited.

publishedTime.name: publishedTime
publishedTime.summary: Specifies the time when a vulnerability was published.

score.name: score
score.summary: Provides a numerical (0-10) representation of the severity of a vulnerability.

severity.name: severity
severity.summary: Specifies the CVSS qualitative severity rating of a vulnerability in relation to a piece of software.

statusNotes.name: statusNotes
statusNotes.summary: Conveys information about how VEX status was determined.

vectorString.name: vectorString
vectorString.summary: Specifies the CVSS vector string for a vulnerability.

vexVersion.name: vexVersion
vexVersion.summary: Specifies the version of a VEX statement.

withdrawnTime.name: withdrawnTime
withdrawnTime.summary: Specified the time and date when a vulnerability was withdrawn.

critical.name: critical
critical.summary: When a CVSS score is between 9.0 - 10.0

high.name: high
high.summary: When a CVSS score is between 7.0 - 8.9

low.name: low
low.summary: When a CVSS score is between 0 - 3.9

medium.name: medium
medium.summary: When a CVSS score is between 4 - 6.9

CvssSeverityType.name: CvssSeverityType
CvssSeverityType.summary: Specifies the CVSS base, temporal, threat, or environmental severity type.

act.name: act
act.summary: The vulnerability requires attention from the organization's internal, supervisory-level and leadership-level individuals. Necessary actions include requesting assistance or information about the vulnerability, as well as publishing a notification either internally and/or externally. Typically, internal groups would meet to determine the overall response and then execute agreed upon actions. CISA recommends remediating Act vulnerabilities as soon as possible.

attend.name: attend
attend.summary: The vulnerability requires attention from the organization's internal, supervisory-level individuals. Necessary actions include requesting assistance or information about the vulnerability, and may involve publishing a notification either internally and/or externally. CISA recommends remediating Attend vulnerabilities sooner than standard update timelines.

track.name: track
track.summary: The vulnerability does not require action at this time. The organization would continue to track the vulnerability and reassess it if new information becomes available. CISA recommends remediating Track vulnerabilities within standard update timelines.

trackStar.name: trackStar
trackStar.summary: (Track* in the SSVC spec) The vulnerability contains specific characteristics that may require closer monitoring for changes. CISA recommends remediating Track* vulnerabilities within standard update timelines.

componentNotPresent.name: componentNotPresent
componentNotPresent.summary: The software is not affected because the vulnerable component is not in the product.

inlineMitigationsAlreadyExist.name: inlineMitigationsAlreadyExist
inlineMitigationsAlreadyExist.summary: Built-in inline controls or mitigations prevent an adversary from leveraging the vulnerability.

vulnerableCodeCannotBeControlledByAdvers.name: vulnerableCodeCannotBeControlledByAdversary
vulnerableCodeCannotBeControlledByAdvers.summary: The vulnerable component is present, and the component contains the vulnerable code. However, vulnerable code is used in such a way that an attacker cannot mount any anticipated attack.

vulnerableCodeNotInExecutePath.name: vulnerableCodeNotInExecutePath
vulnerableCodeNotInExecutePath.summary: The affected code is not reachable through the execution of the code, including non-anticipated states of the product.

vulnerableCodeNotPresent.name: vulnerableCodeNotPresent
vulnerableCodeNotPresent.summary: The product is not affected because the code underlying the vulnerability is not present in the product.

AnyLicenseInfo.name: AnyLicenseInfo
AnyLicenseInfo.summary:
Abstract class representing a license combination consisting of one or more
licenses (optionally including additional text), which may be combined
according to the SPDX license expression syntax.

LicenseExpression.name: LicenseExpression
LicenseExpression.summary: An SPDX Element containing an SPDX license expression string.

SimpleLicensingText.name: SimpleLicensingText
SimpleLicensingText.summary: A license or addition that is not listed on the SPDX License List.

customIdToUri.name: customIdToUri
customIdToUri.summary: Maps a LicenseRef or AdditionRef string for a Custom License or a Custom License Addition to its URI ID.

licenseExpression.name: licenseExpression
licenseExpression.summary: A string in the license expression format.

licenseListVersion.name: licenseListVersion
licenseListVersion.summary: The version of the SPDX License List used in the license expression.

licenseText.name: licenseText
licenseText.summary: Identifies the full text of a License or Addition.

File.name: File
File.summary: Refers to any object that stores content on a computer.

Package.name: Package
Package.summary: Refers to any unit of content that can be associated with a distribution of software.

Sbom.name: Sbom
Sbom.summary: A collection of SPDX Elements describing a single package.

Snippet.name: Snippet
Snippet.summary: Describes a certain part of a file.

SoftwareArtifact.name: SoftwareArtifact
SoftwareArtifact.summary: A distinct article or unit related to Software.

additionalPurpose.name: additionalPurpose
additionalPurpose.summary: Provides additional purpose information of the software artifact.

attributionText.name: attributionText
attributionText.summary:
Provides a place for the SPDX data creator to record acknowledgement text for
a software Package, File or Snippet.

byteRange.name: byteRange
byteRange.summary: Defines the byte range in the original host file that the snippet information applies to.

contentIdentifier.name: contentIdentifier
contentIdentifier.summary: A canonical, unique, immutable identifier of the artifact content, that may be used for verifying its identity and/or integrity.

contentIdentifierType.name: contentIdentifierType
contentIdentifierType.summary: Specifies the type of the content identifier.

contentIdentifierValue.name: contentIdentifierValue
contentIdentifierValue.summary: Specifies the value of the content identifier.

contentType.name: contentType
contentType.summary: Provides information about the content type of an Element.

copyrightText.name: copyrightText
copyrightText.summary:
Identifies the text of one or more copyright notices for a software Package,
File or Snippet, if any.

downloadLocation.name: downloadLocation
downloadLocation.summary: Identifies the download Uniform Resource Identifier for the package at the time that the document was created.

fileKind.name: fileKind
fileKind.summary: Describes if a given file is a directory or non-directory kind of file.

homePage.name: homePage
homePage.summary: A place for the SPDX document creator to record a website that serves as the package's home page.

lineRange.name: lineRange
lineRange.summary: Defines the line range in the original host file that the snippet information applies to.

packageUrl.name: packageUrl
packageUrl.summary: Provides a place for the SPDX data creator to record the package URL string (in accordance with the [package URL spec](https://github.com/package-url/purl-spec/blob/master/PURL-SPECIFICATION.rst)) for a software Package.

packageVersion.name: packageVersion
packageVersion.summary: Identify the version of a package.

primaryPurpose.name: primaryPurpose
primaryPurpose.summary: Provides information about the primary purpose of the software artifact.

sbomType.name: sbomType
sbomType.summary: Provides information about the type of an SBOM.

snippetFromFile.name: snippetFromFile
snippetFromFile.summary: Defines the original host file that the snippet information applies to.

sourceInfo.name: sourceInfo
sourceInfo.summary:
Records any relevant background information or additional comments
about the origin of the package.

gitoid.name: gitoid
gitoid.summary: Gitoid stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects) and a gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent the software [Artifact ID](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-id) or the [OmniBOR Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#omnibor-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [OmniBOR Document](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#omnibor-document).

swhid.name: swhid
swhid.summary: SoftWare Hash IDentifier, persistent intrinsic identifiers for digital artifacts. The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [SWHID specification](https://www.swhid.org/specification/v1.1/4.Syntax) and in the case of filess they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

ContentIdentifierType.name: ContentIdentifierType
ContentIdentifierType.summary: Specifies the type of a content identifier.

directory.name: directory
directory.summary: The file represents a directory and all content stored in that directory.

file.name: file
file.summary: The file represents a single file (default).

FileKindType.name: FileKindType
FileKindType.summary: Enumeration of the different kinds of SPDX file.

analyzed.name: analyzed
analyzed.summary: SBOM generated through analysis of artifacts (e.g., executables, packages, containers, and virtual machine images) after its build. Such analysis generally requires a variety of heuristics. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as a 3rd party SBOM.

build.name: build
build.summary: SBOM generated as part of the process of building the software to create a releasable artifact (e.g., executable or package) from data such as source files, dependencies, built components, build process ephemeral data, and other SBOMs.

deployed.name: deployed
deployed.summary: SBOM provides an inventory of software that is present on a system. This may be an assembly of other SBOMs that combines analysis of configuration options, and examination of execution behavior in a (potentially simulated) deployment environment.

design.name: design
design.summary: SBOM of intended, planned software project or product with included components (some of which may not yet exist) for a new software artifact.

runtime.name: runtime
runtime.summary: SBOM generated through instrumenting the system running the software, to capture only components present in the system, as well as external call-outs or dynamically loaded components. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as an Instrumented or Dynamic SBOM.

source.name: source
source.summary: SBOM created directly from the development environment, source files, and included dependencies used to build an product artifact.

SbomType.name: SbomType
SbomType.summary: Provides a set of values to be used to describe the common types of SBOMs that tools may create.

application.name: application
application.summary: the Element is a software application

archive.name: archive
archive.summary: the Element is an archived collection of one or more files (.tar, .zip, etc)

bom.name: bom
bom.summary: Element is a bill of materials

container.name: container
container.summary: the Element is a container image which can be used by a container runtime application

device.name: device
device.summary: the Element refers to a chipset, processor, or electronic board

deviceDriver.name: deviceDriver
deviceDriver.summary: Element represents software that controls hardware devices

diskImage.name: diskImage
diskImage.summary: the Element refers to a disk image that can be written to a disk, booted in a VM, etc. A disk image typically contains most or all of the components necessary to boot, such as bootloaders, kernels, firmware, userspace, etc.

evidence.name: evidence
evidence.summary: the Element is the evidence that a specification or requirement has been fulfilled

executable.name: executable
executable.summary: Element is an Artifact that can be run on a computer

file.name: file
file.summary: the Element is a single file which can be independently distributed (configuration file, statically linked binary, Kubernetes deployment, etc)

filesystemImage.name: filesystemImage
filesystemImage.summary: the Element is a file system image that can be written to a disk (or virtual) partition

firmware.name: firmware
firmware.summary: the Element provides low level control over a device's hardware

framework.name: framework
framework.summary: the Element is a software framework

install.name: install
install.summary: the Element is used to install software on disk

library.name: library
library.summary: the Element is a software library

manifest.name: manifest
manifest.summary: the Element is a software manifest

model.name: model
model.summary: the Element is a machine learning or artificial intelligence model

module.name: module
module.summary: the Element is a module of a piece of software

operatingSystem.name: operatingSystem
operatingSystem.summary: the Element is an operating system

other.name: other
other.summary: the Element doesn't fit into any of the other categories

patch.name: patch
patch.summary: Element contains a set of changes to update, fix, or improve another Element

requirement.name: requirement
requirement.summary: the Element provides a requirement needed as input for another Element

source.name: source
source.summary: the Element is a single or a collection of source files

specification.name: specification
specification.summary: the Element is a plan, guideline or strategy how to create, perform or analyse an application

test.name: test
test.summary: The Element is a test used to verify functionality on an software element

SoftwarePurpose.name: SoftwarePurpose
SoftwarePurpose.summary: Provides information about the primary purpose of an Element.
